@node Description

	@{b}DESCRIPTION@{ub}
	Some  programs requst Fast RAM specificly, these programs will fail
	on  a  Chip  RAM  only Amiga.  AnyMEM will make sure that this wont
	happen.   Whenever  a program requests Fast RAM, AnyMEM will change
	this  request  to  ask  for the best available memory on your Amiga
	instead.  So if you have enough free Fast RAM, it will use Fast RAM
	as  a  first priority.  If no Fast RAM is present, Chip RAM will be
	used.
@endnode
@node Installation

	@{b}INSTALLATION@{ub}
	Copy the file 'AnyMEM' to your 'C:' directory.
@endnode
@node Usage

	@{b}USAGE@{ub}
	Run it once to install, and once again to remove.
@endnode
